data.name: BBQ Chicken Tacos with Creamy Avocado Sauce
data.quickTastyDescription: Flavorful BBQ chicken wrapped in soft tortillas, topped with a creamy avocado sauce for a delicious twist.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook the chicken thighs in a skillet over medium heat for about 6-8 minutes on each side, or until fully cooked.
Once cooked, shred the chicken and mix with BBQ sauce until fully coated.
Warm the corn tortillas in a dry skillet for about 30 seconds on each side.
Prepare the creamy avocado sauce by blending avocado, Greek yogurt, lime juice, cilantro, salt, and pepper until smooth.
Assemble the tacos by placing shredded BBQ chicken on each tortilla and drizzling with avocado sauce.
